We Claim :<br>
1.	A method for storing audio-centered information on a unitary storage medium while<br>
using a non-hierarchical Table-of Contents (TOC) mechanism for therein specifying an actual<br>
configuration of audio items on said medium,<br>
being characterized by assigning one or more Sub-TOCs to each of a plurality differently standardized audio formats, and furthermore providing a single Master-TOC specifically pointing to each of said sub-TOCs.<br>
2.	A method as claimed in claim 1, wherein the number of sub-TOCs is exactly 2.<br>
3.	A method as claimed in claim 1, and furthermore providing said Master-TOC at a<br>
standard offset location with respect to an initial location of said medium.<br>
4.	A method as claimed in claim 1, wherein said audio formats comprise at least a<br>
Stereo format and at least one Multi-Channel audio format.<br>
5.	A method as claimed in claim 1, and furthermore providing at least one of said TOC<br>
and sub-TOC in at least two copies for reason of safety.<br>
6.	A unitary medium with stored thereon audio-centered information and a non-<br>
hierarchical Table-Of-Content for therein specifying an actual configuration of audio items on<br>
said medium,<br>
characterized in that the Table-of-content comprises one or more Sub-TOCs assigned to each of a plurality of differently standardized audio formats, and<br>
A single Master-TOC for specifically pointing to each sub-TOC.<br>
7.	A unitary medium as claimed in claim 6, characterized in that, the number of Sub-<br>
TOCs is exactly 2.<br>
8.	A unitary medium as claimed in claim 6, characterized in that, said Master-TOC is<br>
located at a standard offset location with respect to an initial location of said medium.<br><br>
10<br>
9.	A unitary medium as claimed in claim 6, characterized in that said audio formats<br>
comprise at least a Stereo format and at least one multi-channel audio format.<br>
10.	A unitary medium as claimed in claim 6, characterized in that, the medium is<br>
provided with at least one of said TOC and sub-TOC with at least two copies for reason of<br>
safety.<br>
11.	A reader device for interfacing to a unitary storage medium as claimed in claim 6,<br>
comprising a read head for scanning the audio centered information stored on the unitary<br>
storage medium, reading means for retrieving date from the scanned information, data<br>
selection means for selecting data from the retrieved data, decoding means for decoding the<br>
selected data, outputting means for outputting the decoded data and control means adapted<br>
for operating said means to handle data formatted according to a specific audio format after<br>
reading a non-hierarchical Table-Of Content information, characterized in that the reader<br>
device is adapted to handle data formatted according to at least a second, differently<br>
standardized audio format using information stored in a single Master-TOC to read data<br>
stored in at least two Sub-TOCs, each corresponding to a different audio format.<br>
12.	A device claimed in claim 11, wherein said unitary storage medium is executed as an<br>
optically readable disc, the read head is of the optical type, provided with disc hold means<br>
and disc drive means for driving the disc along a track along said read head of the optical<br>
type.<br>
Audio information is stored on a unitary storage medium with a Table-of-Contents (TOC) mechanism for therein specifying an actual configuration of various audio items on the medium, In particular, one or more Sub-TOCs are each assigned to a respective different audio format. A single Master-TOC is provided for specifically pointing to each Sub-TOC.</td>
